keel.Algorithms.Rule_Learning.Slipper

Class Score

  • java.lang.Object
    • keel.Algorithms.Rule_Learning.Slipper.Score

  • public class Score
extends java.lang.Object
    Representation of a Trio's vector. It counts the number of instances (positive and negative) that contains each value for a given attribute in a dataset. Each element is a Trio in the form: {value,positives,negatives}

    Since:
    JDK1.2

    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    Written by Alberto Fernández (University of Granada) 01/07/2008, Modified by Xavi Solé (La Salle, Ramón Llull University - Barcelona) 03/12/2008

      • addKey

        public void addKey(double key,
                   double value,
                   int sign)
        Adds a new value to the vector. The number of positive and negative instances are initialize to 0 or 1 wether the sign is POSITIVE or NEGATIVE.
        Parameters:
        key - double the new value
        value - the adding value
        sign - int it indicates wich of the measures will be intialized to 1 (the other will be initialized to 0)
